    • Method Detail

      • getObjectCursor

        public static <T> ObjectCursor<T> getObjectCursor(android.database.Cursor cursor)
        Convert a standard Android Cursor into a ObjectCursor.
        This is only possible for Cursors that where queried over a ContentResolver from a ContentProvider derived by BaseContentProvider.
        Type Parameters:
        T - Entity class represented within the Cursor
        Parameters:
        cursor - Android Cursor
        Returns:
        The ObjectCursor representation of the given Android Cursor
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - When the given cursor is null
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - When the given cursor is not of the type CursorWrapper, which will be returned by a ContentResolver
        java.lang.IllegalStateException - When the wrapped cursor within the given cursor is not of type ObjectCursor. This indicates that the given cursor was not queried from a derivation BaseContentProvider
